<p>During the show, the TV star and Yinka were joined by the likes of Fearne Cotton, Millie Mackintosh and Julien Macdonald. </p>

<p>Elsewhere, the television star spoke to Managing Director of Boots UK and ROI, Seb James, who said stores are introducing a series of measures both in-store and online to adapt to the coronavirus pandemic.</p>

<p>It includes out of hours shopping for over 60s, the return of 3 for 2 offers, more value deals than ever before and thousands of gifts under £10.   </p>

